<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-06T02:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-06T02:30:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/6</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WCS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-06T10:00:00+02:30">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11:30 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Department’s August 4, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d101fn1">See footnote,
                                    <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_42">p.
                                42</ref>.</note> Have asked audience through Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs stating reason. He replied offer comes too late for Russia,
                            should have been made earlier. Austria only country where it can help
                            now. Audience with the Emperor uncertain on account of numerous
                            engagements and approaching departure for Moscow where he will remain
                            some time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WCS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>